cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is focused on analyzing the properties of word embeddings and their impact on downstream NLP tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper evaluates the embeddings on intrinsic and extrinsic tasks, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the geometric properties of the embeddings, which could be relevant to neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to computer vision tasks that involve natural language processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a potential sub-category.
